nit, coding standard says don't do this.

you COULD do
namespace match = sdbusplus::bus::match;

we hit this same problem in other sensors on a config replacement.

The old device exists, and we can't really create a new device until the old device (and the resources it uses) are destroyed.

that's why in most of the other sensors you'll see something like

devices[inventory] = nullptr;
devices.emplace(...);


I suspect we need the same thing here.
